Identity Providers offer various registration options, either free of charge or for a fee, and their respective SPIDs have different security levels. Here are some useful factors to consider if you don’t yet have a SPID and are deciding which Identity Provider to use:

- The verification method that is most convenient for you during the application process (in person, via Electronic ID Card (CIE)*, National Services Card (CNS), digital signature, or via webcam);
- Your desired SPID security level;
- If you’re already a customer of one of the Identity Providers, you may be eligible for a simplified registration process;
- If you’re an Italian citizen living abroad, be sure to check which providers offer services for residents abroad.

For more information, visit the [SPID](https://www.spid.gov.it/cos-e-spid/come-attivare-spid/) website.

